Backend:
make an abstract player class
make a derivative human player class and a ai player class, the human player class will have methods that use user inputs
make a method to place the chip based on user input for human class, and an algorithm for the ai player
use an 2d array property of booleans to keep track of chip positions on the board
Make a method to check if the player won by checking for horizontal, vertical, and diagnol win conditions


Frontend:
Set up the game board with 7 columns and 6 rows, the user wil be asked to place a chip in one of the seven columns and the chip will be placed at the lowest possible row
Use writeline function to represent the board, use a dash for empty spaces and a asterisk for filled position

